Wash and dry all produce. Lightly oil a #baking sheet{} and place in oven on
upper rack. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Halve @Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%oz}.
Halve and peel @Shallot{4%tbsp}, then finely chop. Pick @Parsley{1/4%oz}(leaves
picked from stems) leaves from stems. Finely chop leaves and stems, keeping
them separate. Pick 1 tsp @Thyme{1/4%oz}(leaves picked, sprigs reserved).

Halve @Multicolored Fingerling Potatoes{4%oz} lengthwise. Toss with a large
drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%tsp} and season with plenty of @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Carefully remove baking sheet from oven and arrange potatoes on it
cut-side down, keeping them toward one side of sheet. Nestle half the thyme
sprigs amongst potatoes (use the rest as you like). Roast in oven
~{10%minutes}.

After 10 minutes, remove potatoes from oven and flip, keeping toward one side
of baking sheet. Toss @Broccoli Florets{16%oz} with a drizzle of olive oil,
salt, and pepper and arrange on other side of sheet. Return to oven and roast
until potatoes are tender and broccoli is beginning to char at edges, about
~{20%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, put @Pine Nuts{1%oz} in a large pan and place over medium-high heat.
Toast, tossing often, until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}.
Heat a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Pat
@Sirloin Steak{20%oz} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season with plenty of salt and
pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Remove
from pan and set aside to rest on a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Place same pan over medium-high heat. Add shallot and a drizzle of olive oil.
Cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @Beef Demi-Glace{1%unit},
tomatoes, and 1/2 cup @water{1/2%cup}. Bring to a simmer, then remove from
heat. Stir in reserved thyme leaves, half the parsley leaves, and
@Butter{2%tbsp}(plain). Season with salt and pepper. Stir in any juices
released by steak. Once done, remove potatoes and broccoli from oven. Heat
broiler to high.

In a #large bowl{}, toss potatoes with @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tbsp} and parsley
stems. Sprinkle @Parmesan Cheese{1/2%cup} over broccoli on sheet. Place under
broiler to melt, ~{2-3%minutes}. Divide steak, potatoes, and broccoli between
plates. Sprinkle pine nuts over broccoli. Spoon sauce over steak. Top with
rest of parsley leaves.

> This recipe brings a steakhouse-quality feast to your dinner table, complete
> with a rich tomato gravy and sophisticated sides garnished with pine nuts and
> thyme.